### Alert is-dismissible

You can make use of the `mars-button-close` component by adding the class `is-dismissible`.

<% example_html do %>
<div class="alert is-dismissible">
  <h4>This is an alert sample!</h4>
  You can add <a href="#">links</a> or texts with <strong>format</strong>
  <button class="button-close"></button>
</div>
<% end %>


### Multiple alerts

To generate multiple alerts you can use the generic @mixin <%= link_to 'mars-build-component', '/documentation/builders/mars-build-component' %>, visit the page on the builder to better understand how it works and arguments.

The `$mars-alerts` element contains the variations written on a map and its name is generated by adding the prefix that we pass to the mixin.

In this case we add the first empty element to directly use the prefix as an element, so using this builder it is preferable that we do not add the mars-alert to another element that is not the element to be extended in this case `%alert`, thus we will obtain less duplicities of css in the result.


<% example_html do %>
<div class="alert">
  JPEG, PNG, GIF or BMP - 5MB file limit, at least 250x250 pixels.
</div>

<div class="alert-success">
  Something really bad has happened.
</div>

<div class="alert-warning">
  This is fine and requires notification
</div>
<% end %>
